The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at Our Lady of Guadalupe Catholic Church in Miami, Florida, expressing the US government's support for the people of Venezuela in their fight for democracy. Pence discussed his recent trip to Latin America and praised the region's progress towards freedom and prosperity. He also highlighted the importance of addressing the drug trade and transnational crime in Latin America. Pence emphasized the US commitment to take action against the Maduro regime in Venezuela, including issuing sanctions and supporting efforts to restore democracy in the country. He called on other countries in the region to do more to isolate and punish the Maduro regime. Pence concluded his speech with a prayer for the people of Venezuela and a hope for a future of freedom in Latin America.